      "content": "but that's the thing, it's not a feeling. it's just a fact. there's no 'me' to find. it's like looking at a hollow shell. if there's nothing left inside, then what's the point of all this pretending? everything just feels so heavy and pointless when you're just playing a part for a world you aren't even part of.",
